JOHANNESBURG - The Sunday Independent is reporting that former finance minister Pravin Gordhan is the source of information for the much-talked-about book "The President's Keepers".
	
	The paper is reporting that author Jacques Pauw never intended to write the book until he was approached by Gordhan. WATCH: Pauw unpacks The President's Keepers Earlier in the week, Sunday Independent sent a list of questions to Pauw, Gordhan and former spy boss Mo Shaik about allegations surrounding the publication. Pauw and Gordhan said they were seeking legal opinion and would not be commenting. The book portrays the country as a shadow mafia state. Pauw has described Sunday Independent editor Steve Motale as discreditedÂ and says his information was planted on him. eNCA